## 1. Project Context

The Nexus app is a LinkedIn-redesign SPA built with **vanilla HTML/JS/CSS** on the frontend and a **single Flask backend** ([backend/app.py](file:///c:/Users/dhyan/OneDrive/Desktop/linkedin-redesign/backend/app.py)). Both user stories in this sprint add AI-assisted outreach capabilities to that backend. A single [outreach.py](file:///c:/Users/dhyan/OneDrive/Desktop/linkedin-redesign/backend/outreach.py) module contains all business logic for both stories so there are no redundant dependencies.

### Chosen User Stories

| # | Story | Assigned To |
|---|-------|-------------|
| 1 | Outreach Message Guidance | Dhyani Soni |
| 7 | Outreach Readiness Check | Victor Jimenez |

**Story #1 GitHub Issue:** https://github.com/dhy-ani/linkedin-clone/issues/2  
**Story #7 GitHub Issue:** https://github.com/dhy-ani/linkedin-clone/issues/3  

---

## 2. Harmonized Backend Overview

Both stories live inside the **same Flask process** and share:

| Concern | Choice | Rationale |
|---------|--------|-----------|
| Language | Python 3.11 | Already used |
| Framework | Flask 3.0 + flask-cors 4.0 | Already in [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Users/dhyan/OneDrive/Desktop/linkedin-redesign/backend/requirements.txt) |
| Data store | In-memory dicts (P4) | No external DB needed for mock phase |
| AI calls | Mocked locally (P4) ‚Üí Amazon Bedrock (P5) | Free AWS credits; avoids vendor lock-in |
| Transport | JSON over HTTP | Consistent with existing API shape |
| Auth | Simulated (user ID = 1 hardcoded as CURRENT_USER) | Matches P4 convention |
| Max simultaneous users | 10 | Flask dev server adequate; production ‚Üí Gunicorn 4 workers |

### New Files

```
backend/
  app.py          ‚Üê add 2 new route groups (no other file changed)
  outreach.py     ‚Üê NEW ‚Äî all business logic for Stories #1 & #7
```

### New Endpoints Summary

| Method | Path | Story | Description |
|--------|------|-------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/api/outreach/generate` | #1 | Generate a message draft |
| `GET`  | `/api/outreach/readiness` | #7 | Profile readiness score |

