## 3. Story #1 ‚Äî Outreach Message Guidance

### 3.1 User Story
> *As a student job seeker, I want help drafting my first LinkedIn message so that I feel confident reaching out to professionals without sounding awkward.*

### 3.2 Acceptance Criteria

| # | Criterion |
|---|-----------|
| AC-1 | User can select a recipient from existing users in the system |
| AC-2 | User can choose a tone: `professional`, `friendly`, or `formal` |
| AC-3 | User can specify an outreach goal: `job_inquiry`, `networking`, `advice`, `collaboration` |
| AC-4 | User can optionally add a custom note (‚â§ 200 characters) |
| AC-5 | Backend returns a draft message ‚â§ 500 characters |
| AC-6 | Backend returns 3 writing tips and 2 alternative openers |
| AC-7 | Missing `recipientId` returns HTTP 400 |
| AC-8 | Non-existent `recipientId` returns HTTP 404 |

### 3.3 API Contract

#### `POST /api/outreach/generate`

**Request Body** (JSON):

```json
{
  "recipientId": 5,
  "tone": "professional",
  "goal": "job_inquiry",
  "custom_note": "I saw your talk at Config 2025!"
}
```

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Constraints |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `recipientId` | `int` | ‚úÖ Yes | ‚Äî | Must match a known user ID |
| `tone` | `string` | No | `"professional"` | `"professional"` \| `"friendly"` \| `"formal"` |
| `goal` | `string` | No | `"networking"` | `"job_inquiry"` \| `"networking"` \| `"advice"` \| `"collaboration"` |
| `custom_note` | `string` | No | `""` | Max 200 characters; appended verbatim |

**Success Response** `200 OK`:

```json
{
  "draft": "Hi Michelle,\n\nMy name is Alex, and I came across your profile and was impressed ...",
  "char_count": 312,
  "tone": "professional",
  "tips": [
    "Keep your message under 300 characters ‚Äî shorter notes have a 3√ó higher reply rate.",
    "Mention a specific detail from their profile to show you've done your homework.",
    "End with a low-commitment ask (e.g., 'open to a quick chat?') not 'let's hop on a call'."
  ],
  "alternatives": [
    "Hi Michelle, I admire your work and would love to connect briefly.",
    "Hey Michelle ‚Äî your background in Design Lead caught my attention!"
  ]
}
```

**Error Responses:**

| Status | Body | Trigger |
|--------|------|---------|
| `400` | `{"error": "recipientId is required"}` | Missing `recipientId` |
| `404` | `{"error": "User 99 not found"}` | Unknown user ID |

### 3.4 Internal Logic ‚Äî `outreach.generate_outreach_message()`

```
Input:  sender (CURRENT_USER dict), recipient (user dict), context (dict)
Output: { draft, char_count, tone, tips, alternatives }

1. Validate tone (default "professional")
2. Extract sender first name, title from headline
3. Extract recipient first name, role, company from experience[0]
4. Build goal_lines dict (4 templates keyed by goal)
5. Append custom_note if present
6. Assemble draft from opener + body + closer
7. Generate 3 static tips
8. Generate 2 alternative openers using recipient.first_name and role
9. Return assembled response dict
```

> **P4 ‚Üí P5 upgrade path:** Replace step 4‚Äì8 with a call to `boto3.client("bedrock-runtime").invoke_model()` using `amazon.titan-text-express-v1` or `anthropic.claude-3-sonnet`. The function signature and response schema do not change.

