## 10. Testing Plan

### Story #1 Tests (can be run with `curl` or a test script)

| Test | Input | Expected Output |
|------|-------|-----------------|
| Valid request | `{ "recipientId": 5, "tone": "friendly", "goal": "networking" }` | `200`, `draft` non-empty, `tips` has 3 items |
| Missing recipientId | `{}` | `400` |
| Unknown recipientId | `{ "recipientId": 9999 }` | `404` |
| Invalid tone (fallback) | `{ "recipientId": 5, "tone": "sarcastic" }` | `200`, `tone` in response = `"professional"` |
| Custom note appended | `{ "recipientId": 5, "custom_note": "Hello!" }` | `200`, `"Hello!"` appears in `draft` |

### Story #7 Tests

| Test | Input | Expected Output |
|------|-------|-----------------|
| Current user (complete profile) | `GET /api/outreach/readiness` | `200`, `score >= 75`, `level = "ready"` |
| User with sparse profile | `GET /api/outreach/readiness?userId=12` | `200`, score reflects missing fields |
| Unknown userId | `GET /api/outreach/readiness?userId=9999` | `404` |
| `can_message` threshold | Any user with score ‚â• 60 | `can_message: true` |
| `top_tips` ordering | User missing experience + photo | `experience` tip appears first (weight 20 vs 10) |

### Manual curl Examples

```bash
# Story #1
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/outreach/generate \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"recipientId": 5, "tone": "friendly", "goal": "networking"}' | python -m json.tool

# Story #7
curl -s http://localhost:5000/api/outreach/readiness | python -m json.tool
```

